Five tribes, totaling 989 people, survived the onslaught, including the Onge, Sentinelese, Andamanese, Jarawa, and Shompen.
The Jawara tribe occupies 639 square kilometers on the Andaman islands.
The Indian navy searched for aborigines on the Nicobar islands to prevent their extinction.
Coral reefs may take decades to recover, while mangroves play a crucial role in protecting coastlines.
Mangroves shield against destructive waves, and their absence worsened tsunami impacts.
Efforts are underway to rehabilitate damaged mangroves and establish early warning systems for natural disasters.
